    "content": "nullContent Creation in Marketing Cloud Engagement\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Content Creation in Marketing Cloud Engagement\n CloudPages\n Content Builder\n Get Started with Content Builder\n Content Builder FAQs\n Content Builder Editor Best Practices and Tips\n Upload Files\n Create Emails in Content Builder\n Create Templates\n Email Client Support for Default Templates\n Add Content to a Template\n Complete Create Template Fields\n Lock a Content Area\n Restrict a Content Area\n Modify the Content Area Properties\n Add Content to a Paste HTML Template\n View or Modify a Template\n Single Source Template Strategy\n Create Mobile Messages\n Create Content Blocks\n Create a Code Snippet\n Share Content\n Duplicate Content\n Content Builder Approvals in Marketing Cloud Engagement\n Content Builder Tags\n Sitecore Content\n Content Builder Recycle Bin\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nCONTENT CREATION\nLock a Content Area\n\nFollow these steps to lock content areas in Content Builder. This feature allows you to add content to a template and then lock the content. You cannot change that content when using that template to create an email.\n\nSelect the template in from the Content Builder library.\nClick Edit.\nHover over the title bar of the content area then click the down arrow.\nClick Lock and Save.\nA red lock appears at the top corner of the content and the content is disabled. Choose Lock again to unlock the content area.\nRestrict a Content Area\nFollow these steps to restrict a content area in Content Builder. This action allows the addition of only the specified number and types of content to the content area when creating an email from the template.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\nÂ ",
